Key Match Events: Nathan Lukes drove in the winning run with a double in the eighth inning
George Springer singled off right-hander Andrew Kittredge with one out in the eighth and Lukes followed with an RBI double into the left field corner
Davis Schneider added a two-run home run
Post-Match Reflections: Blue Jays manager John Schneider said the team showed focus and good pitching and defense
Cardinals manager Oliver Marmol said the team hasn't been able to execute offensively and hasn't scored enough runs to win games
Miscellaneous Highlights: Lukes and Kittredge were teammates with Tampa Bay’s Triple-A team in Durham in 2019

Blue Jays second baseman Leo Jiménez turned in the defensive play of the game in the sixth, diving to stop a hard grounder from Luken Baker and flipping to shortstop Ernie Clement to start an inning-ending 6-4-3 double play
